        {
          "question": "Can I apply for my loved one if they can't get to the local office?",
          "answer": "Many CBOs allow family members to apply on behalf of elderly or disabled parents, but policies vary by organization. Call your county's CBO to ask about their representative application process and what additional forms may be needed."
        },
        {
          "question": "What if my loved one's income is slightly over the limit one month?",
          "answer": "LIHEAP uses gross countable income from the previous month only, so temporary income spikes may affect eligibility. However, income limits vary between CBOs, if one organization's limit is too low, check if a neighboring county's CBO has higher limits."
        },
        {
          "question": "How long do LIHEAP benefits last once approved?",
          "answer": "LIHEAP makes a one-time payment directly to your loved one's energy provider for that season. Benefits don't continue automatically, you must reapply for heating assistance (winter), cooling assistance (summer), and crisis assistance as needed throughout the year."
        },
        {
          "question": "Can my loved one apply for LIHEAP and Weatherization Assistance at the same time?",
          "answer": "Yes, these are separate programs that can complement each other. LIHEAP provides immediate bill payment assistance while Weatherization makes long-term home improvements to reduce energy costs. Many CBOs administer both programs."
        },
        {
          "question": "What if my loved one heats with wood or propane instead of electricity or gas?",
          "answer": "LIHEAP covers all energy sources including electricity, natural gas, propane, wood, and pellets. The benefit amount is calculated based on your loved one's primary heating or cooling source, and payments go directly to the fuel vendor or utility company."
        }
